  - m_Id: 26387813197836288
    m_Localized: Welcome to the Survey Area
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26388008295886848
    m_Localized: 'Before archaeologists excavate, they begin with a pedestrian survey.
      This is the first look at a site before even marking out where you are planning
      to dig. The goal is to get an idea of where surface features are located, document
      surface artifacts, and orient yourself with your team within a site.


      The
      traditional method for a pedestrian survey uses transect lines. Team members
      will line up about three or four meters apart along the edge of the site or
      area you are focusing on. Slowly, the team will walk the length of the site
      and scan the ground for any surface artifacts or features and record them properly.
      Due to the singleplayer aspect of this experience, we accomplish this with
      drone work. Please click on the drone to begin the pedestrian survey, or walk
      the site and record information about surface artifacts. There are 6 in total
      that need to be recorded before excavation can begin!'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26388156040245248
    m_Localized: Continue
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26454059964592128
    m_Localized: Left Click to use Drone
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26458016589967360
    m_Localized: 'WASD / Arrows Move:   |   Q / E: Rotate   |   R / F: Angle   |  
      Mouse Wheel: Zoom   |   Space: Exit'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26802534212333568
    m_Localized: Complete the pedestrian survey before excavating.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26830016894365696
